 the potential contribution of educational institutions to the maintenance and retention of Spanish among the current Spanish-speaking population of California.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aBilingualismxCalifornia. 0aLanguages in contactxCaliforniaxCalifornia. 0aSpanish languagexStudy and teaching (Higher)xCalifornia. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aSpanish.  aheritage language.  alanguage education.  aminority language.1 aChavez, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChávez, Rebecca, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aFishman, Joshua A, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aFishman, Joshua A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerez, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aValdes, Guadalup, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aValdes, Guadalupe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978185359899940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781853598999423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781853598999/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  a